Package: dst
Type: Package
Title: Using Dempster-Shafer Theory for Evidence calculus
Version: 0.4
Date: 2018-04-09
Author: Claude Boivin, Stat.ASSQ <webapp.cb@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Claude Boivin <webapp.cb@gmail.com>
Description: This package provides functionalities to make basic chance assignments (bca), namely a mass function, on the subsets (events) of a set of values. The set of values is called a frame a discernment. Two bca's can be combined using Dempster's rule of combination. A bca can be extended to a larger frame. Marginalization, or reduction to a smaller frame can also be done.
License: GPL (>= 2)
BugReports: https://github.com/RAPLER/dst-1/issues
